
@startuml

' Define classes and their attributes

class Employee {
  +String name
  +String socialSecurityNumber
}

class CreativeEmployee <<abstract>> {
}
CreativeEmployee <|-- Director
CreativeEmployee <|-- Actor

class Director {
  +String assistantName
  +boolean hasOscar
}

class Actor {
  +String education
  +boolean hasOscar
}

class Technician {
  +String fieldOfActivity
}

class FilmSet {
  +String location
}

class Film {
  +String title
  +int releaseYear
  +Genre genre
}

enum Genre {
  THRILLER
  ACTION
  HORROR
  COMEDY
}

class Screenwriter {
  +String name
  +String mostSuccessfulFilm
}

class Screenplay {
  +String title
  +int version
  +Date date
  +int numberOfScenes
  +String plot
  +SourceType sourceType
}

enum SourceType {
  NOVEL
  CONCEPT
}

class Novel {
  +String title
  +String author
}

' Relationships

Employee <|-- CreativeEmployee
Employee <|-- Technician

FilmSet "0..*" --> "0..*" Film : used for
Film "1" --> "1" Genre
Film "1" --> "1" Screenplay : based on
Screenplay "1" --> "1" Film : written for
Screenplay "1" --> "1" SourceType
Screenplay "1" --> "1" Novel : if based on novel (optional)

Screenwriter "1" --> "0..*" Screenplay : creates
Screenwriter "1" --> "1" Screenplay : owns

Film "1" --> "0..*" Actor : includes
Film "1" --> "1" Director : directed by
Film "1" --> "0..*" Technician : employs

@enduml

---

### Explanation of Key Elements:

- **Employee**: Base class with `name` and `socialSecurityNumber`.
- **CreativeEmployee**: Abstract class that includes **Director** and **Actor**, both can have an Oscar.
- **Technician**: A non-creative employee with a specific field of activity.
- **FilmSet**: Has a location and can be used for multiple films.
- **Film**: Has a title, release year, and genre. It uses one or more film sets.
- **Screenwriter**: Creates screenplays and has a most successful film.
- **Screenplay**: Written for exactly one film and has a source type (novel or concept).
- **Novel**: Only appears if the screenplay is based on a novel.

